<concept xml:lang="en-us" id="concept_3413BBD173324104B42FB714974CABE7">
                        <title>Managing VAT Rates</title>
                        <conbody>
                                                <section>
                                                            <p>In case you want to invoice usage charges for subscriptions as gross prices, you can enable VAT rate support for your supplier organization. </p>
                                                            <p>You can define a default VAT rate that applies to all prices for all customers. In addition, you can define country-specific or even customer-specific VAT rates. You can:<ul>
                                                            <li><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/Define_a_country-specific_VAT_task_taskbody_context_p_2_u"
                                                            /></li>
                                                            <li><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/Define_a_customer-specific_VA_task_taskbody_context_p_2_u"
                                                            /></li>
                                                            </ul></p>
                                                            <p><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/The_VAT_rate_settings_have_th_task_taskbody_context_p_3_ph"
                                                            /></p>
                                                            <ul>
                                                            <li><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/If_VAT_rate_support_is_disabl_task_taskbody_context_ul_li"
                                                            /></li>
                                                            <li><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/A_customer-specific_VAT_rate_task_taskbody_context_ul_li"
                                                            /></li>
                                                            <li><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/The_country-specific_VAT_rate_task_taskbody_context_ul_li"
                                                            /></li>
                                                            <li><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/The_default_VAT_rate_is_used_task_taskbody_context_ul_li"
                                                            /></li>
                                                            </ul>
                                                            <p>The VAT rate does not affect any price model elements. The calculated VAT amount is added to the overall costs and results in the gross price to be paid by a customer. </p>
                                                            <p><ph
                                                            conref="../../help/tasks/organization_manageVats.xml#task634/If_you_grant_resellers_the_pe_task_taskbody_context_p_5_ph"
                                                            /></p>
                                                            <p>To enable VAT rate support and set the VAT rates for your organization, use the <uicontrol>Manage VAT rates</uicontrol> menu option in the <uicontrol>Customer</uicontrol> menu of the <ph
                                                            conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                                            /> administration portal.</p>
                                                </section>
                        </conbody>
</concept>
